  "prompt": "What is the main function of the brachiocephalic artery?",
  "response": "The main function of the brachiocephalic artery, also known as the innominate artery, is to supply oxygenated blood to the right arm and the head and neck. It branches off from the aortic arch and subsequently divides into the right subclavian artery and the right common carotid artery. The right subclavian artery provides blood to the right arm, while the right common carotid artery supplies blood to the right side of the head and neck. This ensures that these regions receive the necessary oxygen and nutrients to function properly.",
